main event: An object believed to be a 'possibly false star' was submitted for analysis in Gary, Minnesota.
interesting points: The observation lasted for 2-3 minutes., The object was identified as a balloon by the investigation., A rock was reportedly found in relation to the observation and sent for identification., The report came in around the same time as Russian Sputnik debris findings in nearby Wisconsin., The analysis of other samples did not reveal any unusual materials.
sighted object: one object potentially identified as a false star
witness description: Individual submitted a rock and a report for identification.
